						               													<description>Serial Killer - One of the players will become the assassin with an unassailable instinct that has been repressed until now. The assassin will convince one of us to become an accomplice in a terrifying scheme: to eliminate one by one, those who until now have been but friends. The Murderer and accomplice will have to go unnoticed in each crimes, hide their plans from their &amp;#10; prospect victims and proceed without leaving traces nor suspicions.&amp;#10; Will the targets be able to stop the murders in time? overcome their cunning, deception, and trickery of criminal duo? or will the killer and his accomplice end up unpunished and indulge in their bloodlust?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Asesino en Serie is a subtlety role game with three different game modes in the same box:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    A deduction game for 2 to 4 players, with games lasting 10 to 20 minutes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this version each player will receive his role, and a hand of cards that he will have to declare face down, on 6 different columns that stand for 6 possible murders. Strategically they will be placing cards and activating destinies, which means revealing the cards of a column. If 2 or more bad intentions appear, it is considered a murder. If 3 murders are completed then Killer and accomplice wins the game. The murderer is caught when the detective appears at his destination, or both cards are in the same column.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    An occult role-playing game for 5 to 10 players, with games ranging from 30 to 45 minutes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This version of the game is a mafia-style subtlety role-playing game. The murderer and accomplices will succeed if the third murder occurs. If the murderer is caught, tried or killed both accomplice and murderer will have lost the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     &amp;quot;Family size&amp;quot; version of the game for 6 to 12 players, designed to be  played in real time with games lasting from 1 to 15 days.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this version of the game, each player receives a card then  leaves the scene with his role card in his pocket, wallet or wherever he prefers. The person with the killer card must choose an accomplice and kill one person per day by showing him the killer card. Interaction is done using the game's official medium, which is the &amp;quot;Serial Killer&amp;quot; mobile app. The way to win the game for the 3 other players is to accuse the killer or for the killer to kill at least half of the players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
